{"questionId":"29942115","questionHtml":"<p>Explain why the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\">\n  <mi>r</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;makes it appropriate to find the equation of a regression line.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\">\n  <mi>r</mi>\n</math></span> being close to –1 indicates there is strong correlation, so a regression line is appropriate. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"29942115","referenceCode":"EXM.2.SL.TZ0.1d.iii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Explain why the value of r makes it appropriate to find the equation of a regression line.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d.iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.1—Concepts, reliability and sampling techniques","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.10—X on y regression line"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}